1 STATE OF OKLAHOMA
2 2nd Session of the 60th Legislature (2026)
3 HOUSE BILL 3046 By: Tedford
4
5
6 AS INTRODUCED
7 An Act relating to game and fish; amending 29 O.S.
2021, Section 7-208, which relates to payment of
8 administrative fine in lieu of bond; providing
methods of payment of fine; providing timeline for
9 payment of fine; and providing an effective date.
10
11
12 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
13 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 29 O.S. 2021, Section 7-208, is
14 amended to read as follows:
15 Section 7-208. A. Any person arrested for violation of any
16 rule promulgated by the Oklahoma Wildlife Conservation Commission
17 may, in lieu of posting bond, pay an administrative fine equal to
18 one-half (1/2) of the current bond schedule, as prepared by the
19 Administrative Office of the Courts pursuant to Section 1115.3 of
20 Title 22 of the Oklahoma Statutes; such administrative fine shall be
21 payable in person or may be paid online, furthermore the payor shall
22 have seven (7) days from the date of the arrest to pay the
23 administrative fine. The amount of the fine shall be rounded to the
24 nearest five-dollar increment.
Req. No. 14177 Page 1

1 B. Any fines collected pursuant to this section shall be
2 payable to the Department of Wildlife Conservation and shall be
3 deposited in the Wildlife Conservation Fund to be used exclusively
4 for developing, managing, conserving, and protecting wildlife and
5 wildlife habitat.
6 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
